name: Cheryl Waters
responseFromOwnerText:
Dear Cheryl, 

We are truly sorry to hear that you are upset and dissatisfied with our services. At Randy's Pro Tree Service, we strive to provide excellent customer service and high-quality work. We attempted to address your concerns by returning to fixing the hairline cracks caused by the sealer, which can occur due to weather changes and are common with patchwork as opposed to complete concrete replacement.

We want to emphasize that despite these issues with the sealer, the driveway still came out great. It was thoroughly power-washed clean, and all the gaps were properly cleaned out. The hairline cracks in the sealer are an unfortunate but expected outcome given the weather changes and the nature of patching and sealing work vs full replacement.
We regret that we were unable to meet your expectations. Despite our efforts to resolve the situation, we experienced disrespect, profanities towards us, and verbal intimidation over the phone, making it in everyone's best interest to cease further communication.

It's important to note that our business has received personal praise from over 225 families on the same platform where you are calling our business a “sham”. To anyone reading this review, please know that we really are not a “sham”. We have been in business since 2008 and are fully licensed in the state of New Jersy for both home improvement contracting and tree work. We also carry general liability, business and workers compensation insurance and attend industry education courses each year to stay sharp.

We take great pride in our “4.9” rating and are committed to ensuring customer satisfaction. We always strive to make things right. We sincerely wish you the best.

Sincerely,
Randy's Pro Tree Service

name: Tushar Ghosh
responseFromOwnerText:
Dear Tushar,

We sincerely apologize for your experience with Randy's Pro Tree Service, and that our business relationship has ended under such circumstances.

Since we began working together in late 2022, our team has aimed to respond promptly to any issues, including your concerns about billing inaccuracies. That particular issue was solved in one email, once it was confirmed this it wasn’t your property.

As for the lawn service, it was necessary to clean up before mowing to prevent the wood debris on the ground from damaging our equipment or affecting the quality of our work. When we could not agree on compensating for this additional cleanup, it seemed best for both parties to part ways.

We regret that you felt our service came across as arrogant or unprofessional. It was never our intent to give that impression. Our contracts are designed to be flexible, allowing any client to discontinue services at their convenience or displeasure, just as we have chosen in this instance.

We are disheartened to hear about your dissatisfaction and take your feedback seriously as we continually strive to improve our service quality. Thank you for your business over the past year, and we wish you the best with your new landscaping service.

Warm regards,

Randy’s Pro Tree Service Team
text:
From the moment I met Randy he was arrogant and unwilling to address any questions I had for him. Despite his reviews I went with him for 1 year. During that time Randy and his team have broken landscape lamps, (refusing to take ownership even after showing him photos and security footage), sent me wrong bills SEVERAL times, many times i spent my entire day arguing with them that they sent me the wrong bill for over $3000 for the WRONG house. One time they showed me they did work on my house that had a pool when I don't even have a pool. Even after sending them google map satellite photos of my house they continued to argue with me all day wasting my time. I had him trim my hedges and they did such a poor job doing so, I had to call Randy back to correct but he said he doesn't like trim too much even though branches were hitting my living room window. He shows up at my house randomly to address the issue and I wasn't even home or was advised he wanted to speak in person to talk. My lawn looks worse before he took over, the cuts are uneven, their edging work is terrible and they are OVERPRICED! I had several landscapers come to my home to review the work Randy did and were absolutely appalled with the quality of work and what we have paid. Most recently Randy did Spring clean up at my home without my authorization, I NEVER needed Spring clean up before but he decided he was going to charge me for it this year despite no spring clean up being done and in the past he never did it because it wasn't necessary from the fall clean up we did. When I disputed it the charge with their admin, they dropped me as a customer which is ridiculous since I paid Randy on time always and I always communicated with them if I wanted to arrange a payment for later date if the service needed to be performed sooner per his recommendation. So in the one year working Randy, it was the most aggravating unprofessional. Good riddance. Happy to have found another landscaper that prioritizes customer service and quality of work.

Bottom line: save yourself the headache, there are other landscapers in the area that do a better job and have better customer service than Randy and his team.

name: Robert Conkling
responseFromOwnerText:
Dear Robert Conkling,

Thank you for taking the time to leave us feedback. We here at Randy's Pro Landscaping value all comments and take them very seriously.

Upon reading your review, we immediately checked our records to address your concerns. However, we did not find any job completion under the name "Robert Conkling". It is possible there may have been a mistake or perhaps the services were requested under a different name.

If you have indeed used our services and you are dissatisfied, we sincerely apologize and wish to rectify the situation promptly. Please call Randy directly at 732-648-9169. Our goal is to ensure complete satisfaction for every customer, and we're ready to do what it takes to make you happy.

On the other hand, if you haven't used our services, we kindly request that you consider removing the review. Misplaced reviews can create a misleading impression for our potential customers and we strive for accuracy in our online representation.

Regardless, thank you for bringing this matter to our attention, and we look forward to resolving any issues.

Best,
The Team at Randy's Pro Landscaping

If he didn’t come back to finish I’d leave a 1 star review but he even went out of his way to make sure every area was taken care of and came back to pick up a few things.
